Douglas Smith wrote;
>There has been a lot of discussion recently about running imagine on different
>platforms, I think it would be a good idea to create a "Reference" scene, and
>render it on as many different machines as we have access to. We could then
>compile a top 100 of machines & typical render speed.
>
>I invite your comments on,
>
> 1. Is it a worthwhile idea ?

Yes, I think it is.

> 2. What the scene should contain.

Good question. Some primitives, and use as many attribute features as
possible (procedural textures, brushmaps, transparency, reflectivity...)

> 3. What machine info we should collect.

Platform, CPU, FPU, RAM (amount and type), how much RAM was used to render,
renderingtime.....

Also, the results should (IMO) be inluded in the FAQ.
Maybe Paul Thompson (are you out there?) could organize and administrate
this (the guy that manages the IML-Pro (now where did that go?))

