million Imagine users.  This is Impulse's way of saying that they would like 
to see the entire base of MS-DOS machine users become Imagine users 
(approximately 80 million MS-DOS machines in the world currently but that 
includes XT and other configurations not really powerful enough to run 
Imagine).
 

